# BC-2.2.2.2 Public / Private key pairs (3) & signing Tx’s with digital signatures

**Simplified**: like you used to make a mailadres to communicate on the internet, we make public keys. They are based on a random number called “the private key”, to communicate: send and receive transactions on a blockchain. 

How do you sign transactions? Just watch following [short clip]( https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=1&v=xIDL_akeras&feature=emb_logo 
